The implementation correctly delivers all requirements for T008:

- `this.stars = []` initialized, loop creates exactly `starCount = 100` stars
- Each star is placed at random x/y via `Phaser.Math.Between`, with random size (1–3) and random `starSpeed` (0.5–3)
- Stars are rendered as white circles (`this.add.circle(..., 0xffffff, ...)`)
- `update()` scrolls each star downward (`star.y += star.starSpeed`), and wraps it back to `y = 0` with a new random x when it exits the bottom (`star.y > this.sceneHeight`)
- Tests in `tests/battle-scene.test.js` cover all of the above behaviors and have passed